						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Slab set up near the temple of Kalamēśvara.</hi></p>						

						<p>A.D. 1260.</p>						

						<p>This inscription is dated in <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1183</hi> (Current) <hi rend="bold">Raudri, Sravaṇa ba. 5, Thursday,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1260, July 29, Thursday.</hi></p>						

						<p>It records a grant of land made for offerings to god <hi rend="bold">Kalidēva</hi> and for conducting the rite of <hi rend="italic">Vasudhārā</hi> of the gods <hi rend="bold">Vighnēśvara, Kshētrapāḷā and Nārāyaṇadēva.</hi> The grant was made by <hi rend="italic">Mahāpradhāna</hi> <hi rend="bold">Vīriseṭṭi,</hi> son of <hi rend="bold">Gaṇapiseṭṭi.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
